{"atom_id":"ig34_p0395_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":395,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§7.2.1 Trial Arms (TA) – Example 4","atom_type":"FIGURE","verbatim":"[FIGURE: Example Trial 4, Cyclical Chemotherapy Retrospective View — diagram showing Screening Epoch, Treatment Epoch (Drug A/Rest/Repeat and Drug B/Rest/Repeat rows), Follow-up Epoch; arms Drug A and Drug B; Randomization arrow]","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":"pdf_p0395+middle","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.5","ts":"2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0395_a004","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":395,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§7.2.1 Trial Arms (TA) – Example 4","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"For the purpose of developing a TA dataset for this oncology trial, the diagram must be redrawn to explicitly represent multiple treatment and rest elements. If a maximum number of cycles is not given by the protocol, then—for the purposes of constructing an SDTM TA dataset for submission, which can only take place after the trial is complete—the number of repeats included in the TA dataset should be the maximum number of repeats that occurred in the trial. The next diagram assumes that the maximum number of cycles that occurred in this trial was 4. Some subjects will not have received all 4 cycles, because their disease progressed. The rule that directed that they receive no further cycles of chemotherapy is represented by a set of green arrows, 1 at the end of each rest epoch, that shows that a subject \"skips forward\" if their disease progresses. In the TA dataset, each skip-forward instruction is a transition rule, recorded in the TATRANS variable; when TATRANS is not populated, the rule is to transition to the next element in sequence.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.5","ts":"2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0395_a005","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":395,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§7.2.1 Trial Arms (TA) – Example 4","atom_type":"FIGURE","verbatim":"[FIGURE: Example Trial 4, Cyclical Chemotherapy Retrospective View with Explicit Repeats — diagram showing Screening Epoch, Treatment Epoch (Drug A arm: A/Rest/A/Rest/A/Rest/A/Rest with 'If disease progression' skip arrows; Drug B arm: B/Rest/B/Rest/B/Rest/B/Rest with skip arrows), Follow-up Epoch; arms Drug A and Drug B; Randomization arrow]","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":"pdf_p0395+bottom","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.5","ts":"2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"}}
